This paper focuses on the optimal allocation of computing resources in distributed computing, specifically in a MapReduce-type framework. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also utilizes coding techniques, which are commonly studied in Information Theory (cs.IT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses data shuffling, which is relevant to Networked and Internet-based Systems (cs.NI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
